The paper deals with the evolution of small groups in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI) and sociology (cs.SOC). The paper also uses statistical analysis and topology-based prediction models, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the experiments are conducted on a dataset, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB).
